This paper deals with image harmonization using neural networks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces multi-task learning (MTL) to improve the predictive performance and learning efficiency of the harmonization model, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper utilizes natural language processing techniques to describe the methodology and results, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL).
